    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-02-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="469"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Michael H. Herbert</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 66.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of
                    your note of the 6th of February, which I have submitted to the President. He
                    charges me to say that, although he appreciates fully the honor done him by this
                    renewed offer from the British, the German, and the Italian Governments to act
                    as arbitrator between those Governments and that of Venezuela, yet in the
                    present situation, considering that his services in that capacity would not
                    substantially expedite the conclusion of the pending negotiation, he sees no
                    reason for changing the view he has hitherto held, that in such a case the high
                    court of The Hague, <pb facs="0559" n="475" xml:id="pg_475"/> which was created
                    by the principal civilized powers for precisely such emergencies, is preferable
                    to any individual chief of state.</p>
                <p>He requests me, therefore, in expressing his conviction that it would not be best
                    for him to accept the honorable service you have suggested, to express also his
                    grateful appreciation of your confidence.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
